    <h2>About Linda Orloff</h2>
 

  <p>Born 1962, lives and works in Copenhagen, Denmark.</p>

<p>Linda Orloff's background in textile art and stage design can beeen in the highly tactile and even monumentalizing spatial exploitation of the photograph, she has been showing in numerous solo and group exhibitions over the years - like FotoFest International, Houston, Texas; Polaroid as art - The Polaroid Collection's Museet for Fotokunst, Odense, Denmark; Jackson Fine Art, Atlanta, Georgia (with Thomas Joshua Cooper, Kiki Schmidt a.o.); Gallery Edwynn Houk, New York (with Sally Mann, Andy Warhol, Joel-Peter Witkin a.o.); Blind Spot and Art Directors' Gallery, New York; Galleri SoHo Triad Fine Arts, New York; Finnish Museum of Photography, Helsinki, Finland; Kristianstad Konsthall, Sweden as well as museums and galleries in Paris; Stockholm and Copenhagen.</p>

<p>Furthermore she has recieved the Danish Ministry of Culture's Photographic Book Prize for the artbook "Saga Blot".</p>

<p>Her works are sold to the Danish National Arts Foundation; the Swedish National Arts Foundation; The National Museum of Photography/The Royal Library, Copenhagen; Museet for Fotokunst, Odense;  the Finnish Museum of Contemporary Photography a.o.<br />
</p>

